      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $A \\in \\mathcal{M}_n(\\C)$ telle que $A = A^{-1}$. $A$ est-elle diagonalisable ?\nCalculer $e^A$. ($e^A = \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\frac{A^k}{k!}$)",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A \\in \\mathcal{M}_n(\\C)\\)</span> telle que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A = A^{-1}\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> est-elle diagonalisable ? Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(e^A\\)</span>. (<span class=\"math inline\">\\(e^A = \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\frac{A^k}{k!}\\)</span>)</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e577e8ea-59b9-41b0-abb7-f504df1e2f34",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$A$ est diagonalisable car $A^2=I$. $e^A = (\\ch1)I + (\\sh1)A$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> est diagonalisable car <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A^2=I\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(e^A = (\\ch1)I + (\\sh1)A\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
